    "updated_at": "2014-02-08T19:36:12Z",
    "body": "This looks like the correct fix to me. I intended it to not be an error if `fill` returned a slice of length 0. The `BufferedReader` implementation can pass through 0-length reads because of this.\n\nThis was definitely in error though, because you have genuinely hit an error at the end of a `MemReader` or `BufReader`\n",
